main event: Two observers reported sighting a lighted, round object that appeared to make a sudden stop and start in the sky over Oakland, California on July 21, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 1 minute.
On July 27, 1961, a person observed a bright, silvery object overhead on a south to north course, flying at around 300 mph and 7-10,000 ft altitude.
The object was shaped like an 'I' with the short leg pointing straight up.
There was no sign of exhaust gases, moisture trails, or noticeable sound.
Another observer in July 1961 saw an unusual, irregularly shaped object traveling from south to north overhead, with the most unusual feature being the lack of noise.
sighted object: A round, lighted object and a bright, silvery 'I'-shaped object
witnesses: Two observers in 1963, and two other observers in 1961
